(48, 1, '2015-03-26 09:17:18', '2015-03-26 09:17:18', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_top_wrap">\r\n<div class="span7">\r\n<h2>BACKGROUND <span>INVESTIGATION</span></h2>\r\nPARKER has been involved in numerous investigations for city and county governments involving all types of criminal matters and issues of policy and procedure violations. These types of investigations arise from many different issues such as policy and procedure violations, allegations of misconduct by employees and complaints from citizens. City municipalities, county governments and corporations can resolve specific issues that may or may not rise to the level of a criminal investigation that would involve law enforcement. These issues can be resolved through many different investigative techniques such as interviews, polygraphs and questionnaires. Thefts of assets within corporations are always a concern for management. Depending on the size of the company and the number of employees that have access to certain assets, the number of suspects may be quite large. Polygraphs can be very expensive so other methods are employed to narrow down the scope of the investigation. Parker Investigations utilizes every available technique to properly and efficiently resolve the issue. All of the findings are well documented and provided to management for review and to develop a course of action to develop safeguards for the future.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="span5"><a href="http://parkerproject.local/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/criminal_top.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-55" src="http://parkerproject.local/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/criminal_top-300x199.jpg" alt="criminal_top" width="300" height="199" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="clearfix"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n <div class="row">\r\n        	<div class="inner_mid_wrap">\r\n            	<div class="span12">\r\n                    <h2>\r\n                        We have developed security plans for large corporations, school systems and private individuals\r\n                        <span>comprehensive security plan includes:</span>\r\n                    </h2>\r\n                    \r\n                    <ul>\r\n                        <li>Review of current video system- location of cameras, type of camera utilized, storage of information (cloud based, DVR, capacity), security of stored information.</li>\r\n                        <li>Review key access system.</li>\r\n                        <li>Review exterior and interior physical security- locks, access points, structural barriers.</li>\r\n                        <li>Review of infra structure, security of: heating and cooling units, power, water.</li>\r\n                        <li>Review of emergency evacuation procedures in the event of: bomb threats, barricaded gunman, irate customers and/or spouses and relatives of employees, active shooter.</li>\r\n                        <li>Review of hiring procedures: application forms, background checks/investigations, polygraphs. Many problems can be avoided at this stage.</li>\r\n                        <li>Review of termination procedures. Many problems/injuries/deaths have arisen from this process.</li>\r\n                        <li>Develop and construct "safe rooms". This room may be the difference in the safety of yourself and others.</li>\r\n                        <li>Review security of assets: vehicles, equipment, storage areas, parking areas, ingress and egress points.</li>\r\n                        <li>Develop security protection plans for individuals within the company.</li>\r\n                    </ul>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>', 'Test page', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'test-page', '', '', '2015-03-26 12:56:59', '2015-03-26 12:56:59', '', 0, 'http://parkerinvestigation.local/?page_id=48', 0, 'page', '', 0),
