(101, 1, '2015-03-26 14:21:07', '2015-03-26 14:21:07', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_mid_wrap">\r\n<div class="span12">\r\n<h2>SCHOOL <span>SAFETY CONSULTING</span></h2>\r\n<p>Parker is trained as an A.L.I.C.E. instructor dealing with emergency response by faculty, staff and students in the event of an active shooter within a school. He has also been trained in FEMA Active Shooter Response and was trained as a G.B.I. agent in Active Shooter First Responder. In 1999, he assisted in the 1999 investigation at the Heritage High School shooting in Conyers, GA. Parker was hired as a consultant for the McDuffie County Board of Education in Thomson, Georgia where he created a new department of public safety. This entailed the creation of a complete set of policies and procedures to be implemented by the department. A threat assessment was conducted on all buildings to include each school and stadium and an assessment was given with recommendations. He has also assisted Contemporary Services Corporation in security concerns at the Georgia Dome in Atlanta, Georgia. This training and past experiences allows him to conduct a complete threat assessment of schools and campuses to include the assessment of buildings, classrooms and policies within the school system. The assessment includes written recommendations, aerial photographs of the campus and a coordination plan with local law enforcement.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'About Parker', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-26 14:21:07', '2015-03-26 14:21:07', '', 5, 'http://parker.nisclient.com/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
