(121, 1, '2015-03-26 14:49:58', '2015-03-26 14:49:58', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_top_wrap">\r\n<div class="span7">\r\n<h2>CRIMINAL INVESTIGATIONS</h2>\r\nIf you are charged with a crime, not only is having a good attorney important, but also, it is equally important in having a private investigator with the right kind of experience and knowledge. In some instances, private investigators have never worked in law enforcement. J. Douglas Parker retired from the Georgia Bureau of Investigation with 30 years of experience. During his career, he has investigated over 350 death investigations that have involved murder-for-hire, suicides, accidental and natural death.\r\n\r\nNumerous investigations have been conducted on child abuse, armed robbery, aggravated assault and battery, sexual assault, police officer â€œuse of forceâ€ and embezzlement. He has also worked with many federal agencies such as the FBI, ATF and DEA. Parker has been qualified as an expert witness in several fields concerning criminal justice topics such as interviews and interrogations, search and seizure, and narcotics investigations. This along with his specialized training in many different fields of crime scene examination, interviews and interrogations, evidence collection and statement analysis makes Parker one of the most experience private investigators in the southeast.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="span5"><a href="http://parker.nisclient.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/services1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-38" src="http://parker.nisclient.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/services1.jpg" alt="services1" width="278" height="261" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="clearfix"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_mid_wrap">\r\n<div class="span12">\r\n<h2>Important considerations when charged with a crime that\r\nmay need to be investigated further:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How was the evidence collected? Was it handled properly? How and where was it stored? Who had access to it?</li>\r\n	<li>Were witnesses interviewed? What is there relationship to the victim? What is the background of the witnesses? Were they in a position to really see what they saw? What is the motive of the witness? If there was an audio recording or written statement, a determination may be made as to his/her truthfulness.</li>\r\n	<li>What procedures did law enforcement follow in taking a statement or preparing and administering a photographic line-up?</li>\r\n	<li>If a Taser was deployed in your arrest, do you have all of the reports that law enforcement is required to prepare? Was the arrest or use of force during an arrest caught on the vehicle in-dash camera or body camera of the officer?</li>\r\n	<li>What is the background of the officer? Has he/she had any complaints made to the department or the Peace Officerâ€™s Standards of Training?</li>\r\n	<li>Was there an informant involved in your case? How was that informant compensated? Were all contacts with the informant properly documented?</li>\r\n	<li>Was there a search warrant utilized? How did the officer obtain information for the warrant? Was information in the warrant corroborated? Did the officersâ€™ conduct any independent investigation?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_bottom_wrap">\r\n<div class="span7">\r\n<h2>Allow Parker Investigations to address these and other concerns when you are charged with any crime.\r\nWe can provide the following:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Review and make recommendations on all paperwork, reports, videos and audio recordings of witnesses, victims, other suspects.</li>\r\n	<li>Review reports generated by law enforcement and determine what may be areas of deficiency in the investigation.</li>\r\n	<li>Re-interview witnesses, victims, additional suspects and officers involved in the case.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide an assessment of crime scene photos and videos.</li>\r\n	<li>Re-visit scenes and make an assessment of them based on the information provided by reports.</li>\r\n	<li>Collect additional physical evidence and properly store that evidence in accordance with the rules of evidence.</li>\r\n	<li>Locate and properly interview new witnesses.</li>\r\n	<li>Locate and properly obtain new evidence in support of your case.</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct background checks on all involved in the case.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform additional DNA, computer/cellphone forensics, audio/video forensics and other laboratory tests.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform additional investigative actions as additional information is obtained.</li>\r\n	<li>Court testimony and "Expert Testimony" in several criminal justice fields.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="span5"><a href="http://parker.nisclient.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/services1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-38" src="http://parker.nisclient.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/services1.jpg" alt="services1" width="278" height="261" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="clearfix"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Criminal Investigation', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-26 14:49:58', '2015-03-26 14:49:58', '', 7, 'http://parker.nisclient.com/7-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(123, 1, '2015-04-01 13:56:48', '2015-04-01 13:56:48', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_top_wrap">\r\n<div class="span12">\r\n<h2>SCHOOL <span>SAFETY CONSULTING</span></h2>\r\nParker is trained as an A.L.I.C.E. instructor dealing with emergency response by faculty, staff and students in the event of an active shooter within a school. He has also been trained in FEMA Active Shooter Response and was trained as a G.B.I. agent in Active Shooter First Responder. In 1999, he assisted in the 1999 investigation at the Heritage High School shooting in Conyers, GA. Parker was hired as a consultant for the McDuffie County Board of Education in Thomson, Georgia where he created a new department of public safety. This entailed the creation of a complete set of policies and procedures to be implemented by the department. A threat assessment was conducted on all buildings to include each school and stadium and an assessment was given with recommendations. He has also assisted Contemporary Services Corporation in security concerns at the Georgia Dome in Atlanta, Georgia. This training and past experiences allows him to conduct a complete threat assessment of schools and campuses to include the assessment of buildings, classrooms and policies within the school system. The assessment includes written recommendations, aerial photographs of the campus and a coordination plan with local law enforcement.\r\n<h2>DEATH INVESTIGATIONS</h2>\r\nThe owner of Parker Investigations, J. Douglas Parker, was employed with the Georgia Bureau of Investigation for 30 years. During his career, he has investigated over 350 deaths involving natural, accidental, suicide, police officer "use of force" and murder, some resulting in the death penalty. These investigations have involved the securing of search warrants in accordance with the 4th amendment, the processing and documentation of crime scenes and attending autopsies. Parker has interviewed in excess of 35,000 witnesses, victims and suspects in a vast array of cases from juvenile misdemeanors to felonies. He has been trained in nonverbal communication and statement analysis which coupled together can provide for an accurate assessment of witness, victim and suspect statements.\r\n<h2>UNDERCOVER NARCOTICS</h2>\r\nParker has extensive experience in undercover narcotics investigations. He served as the Regional Narcotics Specialist investigating major level traffickers in state and federal jurisdictions. Through these undercover investigations, Parker has been trained in the most advanced technology and utilized undercover surveillance techniques.\r\n<h2>DIGNITARY PROTECTION</h2>\r\nTrained by the Secret Service, Parker was assigned to numerous presidential and heads-of-state protection details. These details have included Jimmy Carter, Bill Clinton, Jesse Jackson and heads-of-state from Austria, Cuba and other countries. While Newt Gingrich was speaker of the house, Parker assisted in the planning and implementation of Mr. Gingrich''s security detail while he was in Georgia.\r\n<h2>CORPORATE SECURITY CONSULTATIONS</h2>\r\nOver the course of his law enforcement career, Parker has assisted in the security plan for the Georgia-Pacific building in Atlanta Georgia, provided security consultations to Chick-Fil-A and made recommendations after a policy review of the city of Sardis, Police Department. Parker authored and implemented a security plan for the Georgia World Congress Center during the 1996 Olympics. Parker was then assigned to the Paralympics as the Assistant Venue Commander over a two event venue.\r\n<h2>HIGH PROFILE/ BACKGROUND INVESTIGATIONS</h2>\r\nNumerous background investigations have been conducted on governor appointed positions and potential employees. During his career, Parker has investigated allegations of wrongdoing by political officials and government appointed personnel. In 1988, Parker was assigned to the Democratic National Convention in Atlanta Georgia on a team of investigators that were responsible investigating complaints and/or allegations made against law enforcement officers.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'About Parker', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-01 13:56:48', '2015-04-01 13:56:48', '', 5, 'http://parker.nisclient.com/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
