(160, 1, '2015-04-07 12:58:35', '2015-04-07 12:58:35', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_top_wrap">\r\n<div class="span12">\r\n<h2>SCHOOL SAFETY <span>CONSULTING</span></h2>\r\nParker is trained as an A.L.I.C.E. instructor dealing with emergency response by faculty, staff and students in the event of an active shooter within a school. He has also been trained in FEMA Active Shooter Response and was trained as a G.B.I. agent in Active Shooter First Responder. In 1999, he assisted in the 1999 investigation at the Heritage High School shooting in Conyers, GA. Parker was hired as a consultant for the McDuffie County Board of Education in Thomson, Georgia where he created a new department of public safety. This entailed the creation of a complete set of policies and procedures to be implemented by the department. A threat assessment was conducted on all buildings to include each school and stadium and an assessment was given with recommendations. He has also assisted Contemporary Services Corporation in security concerns at the Georgia Dome in Atlanta, Georgia. This training and past experiences allows him to conduct a complete threat assessment of schools and campuses to include the assessment of buildings, classrooms and policies within the school system. The assessment includes written recommendations, aerial photographs of the campus and a coordination plan with local law enforcement.\r\n<h2>DEATH <span>INVESTIGATIONS</span></h2>\r\nThe owner of Parker Investigations, J. Douglas Parker, was employed with the Georgia Bureau of Investigation for 30 years. During his career, he has investigated over 350 deaths involving natural, accidental, suicide, police officer "use of force" and murder, some resulting in the death penalty. These investigations have involved the securing of search warrants in accordance with the 4th amendment, the processing and documentation of crime scenes and attending autopsies. Parker has interviewed in excess of 35,000 witnesses, victims and suspects in a vast array of cases from juvenile misdemeanors to felonies. He has been trained in nonverbal communication and statement analysis which coupled together can provide for an accurate assessment of witness, victim and suspect statements.\r\n<h2>UNDERCOVER <span>NARCOTICS</span></h2>\r\nParker has extensive experience in undercover narcotics investigations. He served as the Regional Narcotics Specialist investigating major level traffickers in state and federal jurisdictions. Through these undercover investigations, Parker has been trained in the most advanced technology and utilized undercover surveillance techniques.\r\n<h2>DIGNITARY <span>PROTECTION</span></h2>\r\nTrained by the Secret Service, Parker was assigned to numerous presidential and heads-of-state protection details. These details have included Jimmy Carter, Bill Clinton, Jesse Jackson and heads-of-state from Austria, Cuba and other countries. While Newt Gingrich was speaker of the house, Parker assisted in the planning and implementation of Mr. Gingrich''s security detail while he was in Georgia.\r\n<h2>CORPORATE SECURITY <span>CONSULTATIONS</span></h2>\r\nOver the course of his law enforcement career, Parker has assisted in the security plan for the Georgia-Pacific building in Atlanta Georgia, provided security consultations to Chick-Fil-A and made recommendations after a policy review of the city of Sardis, Police Department. Parker authored and implemented a security plan for the Georgia World Congress Center during the 1996 Olympics. Parker was then assigned to the Paralympics as the Assistant Venue Commander over a two event venue.\r\n<h2>HIGH PROFILE/ BACKGROUND <span>INVESTIGATIONS</span></h2>\r\nNumerous background investigations have been conducted on governor appointed positions and potential employees. During his career, Parker has investigated allegations of wrongdoing by political officials and government appointed personnel. In 1988, Parker was assigned to the Democratic National Convention in Atlanta Georgia on a team of investigators that were responsible investigating complaints and/or allegations made against law enforcement officers.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_mid_wrap">\r\n<div class="span12">\r\n<h2>~ ASSOCIATES ~</h2>\r\nJOHN M. VAUGHN\r\n\r\nCriminal Specialist (Retired)\r\n\r\nNC State Bureau of Investigation\r\n\r\n~ Computer Crimes Unit ~\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Conduct criminal investigations involving the sexual exploitation of children as a member of the SBI Internet Crimes Against children (ICAC) Task Force</li>\r\n	<li>Investigate Cybertips received from the National Center for Missing and\r\nExploited Children (NCMEC)</li>\r\n	<li>Plan, coordinate and participate in large scale security events including\r\nGubernatorial Inaugurations and the PGA U.S. Open (1999, 2005)</li>\r\n	<li>Assign and coordinate all background investigations for Bureau employees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n~ Medicaid Fraud Criminal Investigations Unit ~\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Conducted investigation resulting in the largest civil monetary recoupment of 1988 for the NC Medicaid Fraud Criminal Investigations Unit</li>\r\n	<li>Investigated original case involving patient physical abuse by a nursing facility resulting in a 12 count criminal conviction</li>\r\n	<li>Conducted and assisted in criminal investigations resulting in arrests and convictions for numerous criminal violations including rape, murder, burglary, and drug offenses</li>\r\n	<li>Investigated over 100 arson and corresponding insurance fraud cases generating convictions at over twice the average national rate</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'About Parker', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-07 12:58:35', '2015-04-07 12:58:35', '', 5, 'http://parker.nisclient.com/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
