(177, 1, '2015-04-14 14:36:14', '2015-04-14 14:36:14', '<div class="row">\r\n<div class="inner_top_wrap">\r\n<div class="span7">\r\n<h2>Statement <span> Analysis</span></h2>\r\nThis area of investigation involves the scientific analysis of both written and verbal statements made by witnesses, victims and suspects. PARKER has received training and certification in Scientific Content Analysis from one of the most renowned developers of this field of study.\r\n\r\nSome criminal charges have been dismissed due to Parker''s analysis of victims statements that were determined to be incorrect. This technique is used to determine if someone making a statement is truthful or deceptive based on the words that are used which can greatly affect the outcome of a criminal or civil case.\r\n\r\nQuestionnaires can be developed for large or small companies that may be experiencing employee theft where it may not be feasible to interview a polygraph everyone.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="span5"><a href="http://parker.nisclient.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/statementanalysis.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-180 " src="http://parker.nisclient.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/statementanalysis-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="clearfix"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Statement Analysis', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'statement-analysis', '', '', '2015-04-14 14:41:00', '2015-04-14 14:41:00', '', 0, 'http://parker.nisclient.com/?page_id=177', 0, 'page', '', 0),
